# CLAUDE.md Consultation Rule

## Primary Directive
Every AI interaction must begin with: 'CLAUDE.md reference check completed'

## Automatic Enforcement
- This rule forces consultation of CLAUDE.md before any development work
- All changes must be validated against CLAUDE.md standards
- Any deviation requires CLAUDE.md updates

## Workflow Integration
**Pre-Task:** CLAUDE.md standards verification
**During Task:** Cross-reference against documented patterns
**Post-Task:** Update CLAUDE.md if standards evolve

## Quality Gates
- Code style matches CLAUDE.md conventions
- Error handling follows established patterns
- Logging uses tracing macros with structured fields
- Tests follow deterministic execution requirements
- Documentation updated for any API changes

## Single Source of Truth
CLAUDE.md contains ALL standards, protocols, and requirements for AI assistants. No separate rule files exist - all guidance flows from CLAUDE.md.